object.field: Mike has poor eyesight from watching too much television.
Mike wears glasses and staff will encourage him to try other activities.
Mike will improve his independent living skills.
Mike wants to increase his social skills and make new friends.
Mike will clean his room once a week without being reminded to do so (i.e., Independent prompt)
Mike will cook meals 3 nights each week with assistance from a staff member (partial physical prompt)
Mike will increase the time he spends in the dining room from 15 minutes to 1 hour for each meal.
Mike will say hello to 5 people each day.
Mike will decrease the amount of time he spends watching TV each day from 10 hours to 2 hours.
Mike will ask 2 people to join him at his table for each meal.
Staff will document the number of people at each mealtime on behavior worksheets.
